was forever left handicapped when he was shot in a road rage dispute in Boston.  <br>
<br>
When I think of all the hotheads out there who's girlfriends just dumped them, got fired from work, or simply didn't take their prozac-- and they have guns, it just scares me big time.  Honestly, I see no reason in why any common citizen needs a gun, let alone a Glock, magnum, or the semi-automatic stuff you CAN buy in the US. This right to bear arms crap is so outdated, I can't believe lobbyists can actually say it with a straight face.  Are you fighting off Indian attacks from your prairie farm?  Is there really a chance that citizens will have to rise up against government in the year 2002?  I don't think so.  The reasoning that we need guns to protect ourselves from criminals is equally dumb, because its the easy availability of said weapons that allows your average street thug to bear arms.<br>
<br>
To me, being able to walk into a store and walk out ten minutes later with any handgun is &quot;retardedly easy&quot;, and the fact that anything better than a .22 is actually available to be &quot;retardedly stupid&quot;.<br>
<br>
Sorry for the rant if it sounds like one.<br>
<br>
P.S:  palimax you may be right about the strip clubs; I only had a chance to sample one in Dallas and the other in Manhattan.  Neither came close to what i saw in Montreal. I'm sure Las Vegas probably has much better heh.<br>
<br>
