<br>
First, except some minor cases, gun control is a state, not federal, bailwick.  This means what state you live in has a huge impact on what you can own and how easy it is to buy them.<br>
<br>
Second, until relativly recently, the FBI was using a very old, very innaccurate database.  Sometime last year they promised to fix it.  I haven't really been paying attention since.  Here in AZ (I live in the same county as Palimax), until a couple years ago, the Maricopa County Sherrif's Office (thanks Sherrif Joe) was doing a horrible job, and they lost a couple lawsuits after people were killed with weapons obtained &quot;legally&quot; by criminals.<br>
<br>
Third, in most of the US, buying weapons at gunshows is still ridiculously easy.  There was a big debate about this before 9-11, haven't seen too much lately.<br>
<br>
